1
00:00:00,340 --> 00:00:01,970
(All people, incidents,
and backgrounds...)

2
00:00:01,970 --> 00:00:03,580
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

3
00:00:03,640 --> 00:00:05,110
(Also, children were filmed
under production guidelines.)

4
00:00:06,610 --> 00:00:07,910
She's refusing the surgery?

5
00:00:08,610 --> 00:00:11,120
Are you saying
she didn't get the third surgery?

6
00:00:11,350 --> 00:00:13,390
The patient herself refused.

7
00:00:13,520 --> 00:00:16,720
Our Seoul hospital had no choice
but to cancel the procedure.

8
00:00:17,020 --> 00:00:18,920
(Admissions, Registration)

9
00:00:19,290 --> 00:00:22,230
Please, reschedule the surgery.

10
00:00:22,590 --> 00:00:25,200
She needs the surgery quickly
before the cancer spread.

11
00:00:25,300 --> 00:00:28,170
In that case, you need
to convince the patient first.

12
00:00:28,400 --> 00:00:31,000
When patients like Kim Dan Hui
give up on treatment,

13
00:00:31,040 --> 00:00:34,310
it's because they don't want to be
a burden on their families.

14
00:00:34,570 --> 00:00:36,570
Can I see my sister now?

15
00:00:37,010 --> 00:00:39,180
Yes, you should be able to visit her
in Ward B.

16
00:00:53,460 --> 00:00:55,760
- Where could she have gone?
- She was here this morning...

17
00:00:55,760 --> 00:00:57,000
Hold on.

18
00:00:58,130 --> 00:00:59,630
Kim Dan Hui seems to be missing.

19
00:01:24,320 --> 00:01:27,230
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

20
00:01:29,530 --> 00:01:30,530
Dan Hui!

21
00:01:34,200 --> 00:01:35,270
Dan Hui, no!

22
00:01:54,550 --> 00:01:55,620
Dan Hui.

23
00:01:57,190 --> 00:01:58,220
Please, don't do this.

24
00:02:01,330 --> 00:02:02,860
Come to me, please.

25
00:02:06,630 --> 00:02:07,800
Please.

26
00:02:16,340 --> 00:02:17,340
Dan Hui!

27
00:02:35,460 --> 00:02:36,560
How did that happen?

28
00:02:37,760 --> 00:02:39,330
Just come down, please.

29
00:02:39,800 --> 00:02:41,500
Answer me, darn it!

30
00:02:52,840 --> 00:02:53,850
What's this?

31
00:02:58,880 --> 00:03:00,050
Explain yourself. Now.

32
00:03:04,590 --> 00:03:05,690
Jung Ran!

33
00:03:11,000 --> 00:03:14,930
She said she was craving
some tart apples...

34
00:03:19,800 --> 00:03:20,810
Jung Ran?

35
00:03:22,370 --> 00:03:23,370
You can't mean...

36
00:03:24,180 --> 00:03:27,880
That's right. It was that day.

37
00:03:29,680 --> 00:03:32,780
You came to the country house
two months ago.

38
00:03:33,280 --> 00:03:36,550
Two months ago?
The day we had that huge fight?

39
00:03:37,620 --> 00:03:41,690
We may have fought,
but we shared a room that night.

40
00:03:42,290 --> 00:03:45,300
You passed out drunk in the bedroom,
and I did in the kitchen.

41
00:03:45,900 --> 00:03:47,170
And then, we...

42
00:03:47,170 --> 00:03:48,930
I remember it clearly.

43
00:03:52,540 --> 00:03:55,770
What's with that look?

44
00:03:56,210 --> 00:03:59,610
I'm pregnant with the child
you've always wanted.

45
00:03:59,810 --> 00:04:02,650
You having a child with someone else
tore me apart.

46
00:04:03,410 --> 00:04:05,750
That's right. I guess it's true...

47
00:04:05,850 --> 00:04:07,790
that jealousy can lead to pregnancy.

48
00:04:08,790 --> 00:04:12,720
I'm carrying your child too.
The child you've always wanted...

49
00:04:12,790 --> 00:04:14,190
is right here.

50
00:04:23,330 --> 00:04:24,440
Geun Tae.

51
00:04:24,770 --> 00:04:25,770
Yes, sir?

52
00:04:29,170 --> 00:04:32,380
Call Dr. Do and make an appointment.

53
00:04:38,880 --> 00:04:39,880
Yes, sir.

54
00:05:01,740 --> 00:05:03,310
You're pregnant?

55
00:05:04,380 --> 00:05:05,380
How?

56
00:05:07,550 --> 00:05:10,950
After all these months, you show up
like this and don't say a word?

57
00:05:11,220 --> 00:05:13,280
You're so worried about me,

58
00:05:13,790 --> 00:05:16,520
- yet you meant to leave me and die?
- Myung Hui!

59
00:05:16,820 --> 00:05:19,060
Why would you refuse the surgery?

60
00:05:19,190 --> 00:05:22,430
If the cancer spreads,
there'll be nothing we can do.

61
00:05:22,560 --> 00:05:24,930
How could you give up
on your treatment...

62
00:05:25,900 --> 00:05:30,070
- and climb up there to...
- I have to die for you to live.

63
00:05:30,700 --> 00:05:31,770
What?

64
00:05:31,970 --> 00:05:34,770
It's all I've thought about lately.

65
00:05:35,640 --> 00:05:37,810
Why hasn't she come to see me?

66
00:05:37,880 --> 00:05:40,610
Did something bad happen
that she has to hide from me?

67
00:05:40,680 --> 00:05:43,650
Are my medical bills
ruining her life again?

68
00:05:43,720 --> 00:05:44,880
Because of me, is she...

69
00:05:45,350 --> 00:05:46,780
It's not like that.

70
00:05:50,720 --> 00:05:52,060
This baby?

71
00:05:53,320 --> 00:05:55,030
I met someone I love,

72
00:05:56,060 --> 00:05:58,130
and I'm having his child.

73
00:06:01,570 --> 00:06:03,270
Then why are you
only telling me now?

74
00:06:08,070 --> 00:06:09,110
Because I felt guilty.

75
00:06:12,010 --> 00:06:13,710
With you being so sick,

76
00:06:16,180 --> 00:06:18,150
I felt guilty for being the only one
who was happy.

77
00:06:24,090 --> 00:06:25,190
I suppose...

78
00:06:26,120 --> 00:06:28,030
this is my punishment.

79
00:06:29,990 --> 00:06:31,560
When you got better,

80
00:06:32,030 --> 00:06:36,000
I was going to tell you about him,
and vice versa.

81
00:06:37,570 --> 00:06:39,340
You haven't told him about me yet?

82
00:06:42,470 --> 00:06:44,740
I didn't want him
to get the wrong idea.

83
00:06:46,480 --> 00:06:47,980
That I was only with him
because you're sick...

84
00:06:49,010 --> 00:06:52,350
and I needed the money
for your surgery.

85
00:06:53,020 --> 00:06:56,450
I didn't want us
to be like that because...

86
00:06:59,060 --> 00:07:00,530
what I felt for him was real.

87
00:07:02,460 --> 00:07:03,460
Also,

88
00:07:04,660 --> 00:07:08,300
he was always so lonely
because he didn't have a family.

89
00:07:09,570 --> 00:07:13,540
Growing up without parents,
enduring all sorts of indignities...

90
00:07:14,010 --> 00:07:15,010
That's you and me.

91
00:07:15,910 --> 00:07:18,080
It's the perfect jewel for us,
don't you think?

92
00:07:20,580 --> 00:07:21,580
So...

93
00:07:22,610 --> 00:07:25,020
I couldn't say I had a family
when he didn't,

94
00:07:26,320 --> 00:07:29,850
or that I had a twin sister
who was adopted.

95
00:07:32,590 --> 00:07:34,390
After the baby was born...

96
00:07:36,330 --> 00:07:38,730
and we became a real family,

97
00:07:39,560 --> 00:07:40,570
then...

98
00:07:43,570 --> 00:07:47,100
Once he stopped feeling so lonely,

99
00:07:47,770 --> 00:07:49,740
I was going to tell him.

100
00:07:51,910 --> 00:07:53,110
You...

101
00:07:54,180 --> 00:07:55,880
really do love him, don't you?

102
00:07:59,350 --> 00:08:00,890
This baby...

103
00:08:01,850 --> 00:08:04,020
and you as well...

104
00:08:06,620 --> 00:08:08,690
I love you both so much...

105
00:08:10,230 --> 00:08:12,530
that I'll do anything
to protect you.

106
00:08:24,480 --> 00:08:25,480
Dan Hui?

107
00:08:26,080 --> 00:08:27,080
Dan Hui!

108
00:08:27,610 --> 00:08:30,620
Dan Hui, what's wrong? Dan Hui!

109
00:08:30,750 --> 00:08:34,320
Over here. Is anybody there?
Somebody help!

110
00:08:34,390 --> 00:08:35,620
Over here!

111
00:08:35,820 --> 00:08:39,390
Dan Hui, come on.
Dan Hui, what's wrong?

112
00:08:39,460 --> 00:08:41,760
Somebody, please help us!

113
00:08:45,260 --> 00:08:46,460
You recognize her, right?

114
00:08:47,200 --> 00:08:49,630
I saw her going into the ward
over there a little while ago.

115
00:08:50,740 --> 00:08:51,870
What happened?

116
00:08:52,270 --> 00:08:53,640
What's this about?

117
00:08:53,670 --> 00:08:54,670
Oh, right.

118
00:08:56,070 --> 00:08:58,340
I'm on the job
and could use your help.

119
00:09:01,550 --> 00:09:04,650
You must talk to the director first.
Without his permission,

120
00:09:04,720 --> 00:09:06,720
I can't just give out
patient information.

121
00:09:10,820 --> 00:09:14,390
Patient information? That means...

122
00:09:14,930 --> 00:09:17,500
she's a patient here. I see.

123
00:09:18,700 --> 00:09:20,870
This should be enough
to report back.

124
00:09:26,700 --> 00:09:29,810
Wait, should I have said she was
a guardian and not a patient?

125
00:09:30,340 --> 00:09:31,340
Whatever.

126
00:09:31,640 --> 00:09:34,110
It doesn't matter. I can't give out
the information either way.

127
00:09:36,850 --> 00:09:38,150
- What the...
- My gosh.

128
00:09:40,590 --> 00:09:43,520
- I'm sorry.
- Unbelievable.

129
00:09:51,130 --> 00:09:53,630
Congratulations.
You waited a long time,

130
00:09:53,730 --> 00:09:55,270
and a spot finally opened up.

131
00:09:55,730 --> 00:09:58,240
I wasn't expecting
to hear back so suddenly.

132
00:09:59,300 --> 00:10:02,710
It seems like they're rushing
because a spot opened up suddenly.

133
00:10:03,240 --> 00:10:05,740
Here, these are the documents
from the US.

134
00:10:05,740 --> 00:10:07,010
This is all you'll need.

135
00:10:08,580 --> 00:10:09,810
Thank you.

136
00:10:10,350 --> 00:10:12,980
When you said you were preparing
to study in the US,

137
00:10:12,980 --> 00:10:14,550
I assumed you'd specialize
in obstetrics...

138
00:10:14,620 --> 00:10:16,990
or forensic medicine,
since you like it.

139
00:10:17,090 --> 00:10:20,390
I was surprised you chose
a different field like biotech.

140
00:10:20,490 --> 00:10:23,060
I'm thinking of taking over
my father's business.

141
00:10:24,200 --> 00:10:25,200
Really?

142
00:10:26,230 --> 00:10:30,800
Someone as smart and diligent as you
would do well in business, too.

143
00:10:31,100 --> 00:10:33,540
Anyway, you'll need
to wrap things up at the hospital,

144
00:10:33,600 --> 00:10:36,040
so you must have a lot
on your plate.

145
00:10:36,440 --> 00:10:38,810
I'm more worried about my wife
than the hospital.

146
00:10:39,210 --> 00:10:41,780
The departure date is too close
to her delivery date.

147
00:10:41,850 --> 00:10:43,210
I can see that.

148
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:46,050
Still, don't worry too much.

149
00:10:46,050 --> 00:10:48,390
She's with her husband,
who's an obstetrician.

150
00:10:48,450 --> 00:10:49,820
What could possibly go wrong?

151
00:11:03,530 --> 00:11:07,140
It's a real shame.
Her younger sister has cancer,

152
00:11:07,200 --> 00:11:09,510
but she's stubbornly
refusing the surgery.

153
00:11:09,870 --> 00:11:11,740
Oh, really?

154
00:11:20,120 --> 00:11:21,120
Dan Hui!

155
00:11:25,790 --> 00:11:27,860
What is the matter with you?

156
00:11:28,790 --> 00:11:32,700
You need to get your strength back
for your surgery in Seoul.

157
00:11:32,860 --> 00:11:34,930
This is already the third surgery.

158
00:11:35,230 --> 00:11:37,230
This might not even
be the end of it,

159
00:11:38,600 --> 00:11:40,600
and I could end up dying
after a lifetime of surgeries.

160
00:11:42,010 --> 00:11:45,340
I have to be realistic now.

161
00:11:45,440 --> 00:11:47,280
That's why I went up there.

162
00:11:51,750 --> 00:11:52,750
From now on,

163
00:11:53,320 --> 00:11:55,090
take care of your life, not mine.

164
00:12:00,190 --> 00:12:01,690
I said I don't want to.

165
00:12:02,190 --> 00:12:05,030
You were supposed to be
the one to go from the start.

166
00:12:07,930 --> 00:12:10,530
I'm fine here.

167
00:12:11,440 --> 00:12:16,070
You're frail, so go to a good home,
be loved, and get treatment.

168
00:12:16,140 --> 00:12:20,850
No, I don't want to go alone
and leave you behind.

169
00:12:21,450 --> 00:12:23,450
Then are you going to stay like this
and die in pain?

170
00:12:24,350 --> 00:12:27,050
Mom and Dad are gone, so if you die,

171
00:12:27,920 --> 00:12:29,550
I'll be all alone.

172
00:12:51,580 --> 00:12:53,140
Who do you think ruined my life?

173
00:12:53,210 --> 00:12:54,450
Blaming me again, are you?

174
00:12:54,450 --> 00:12:56,450
You were happy
about the adoption too.

175
00:12:56,510 --> 00:12:58,150
Then you should've chosen
a better one.

176
00:12:58,620 --> 00:13:01,390
You adopted a sick, unlucky kid,
and now we're bankrupt.

177
00:13:01,450 --> 00:13:04,420
It was fine when we had money,
but now that we're broke, it's not?

178
00:13:04,490 --> 00:13:07,220
If you'd run your business well,
there wouldn't be a problem!

179
00:13:07,390 --> 00:13:10,460
We shouldn't have adopted her.
Kick her out.

180
00:13:10,530 --> 00:13:12,500
Throw all of her things out!

181
00:13:12,830 --> 00:13:15,870
I'm so sick of this!
Fine, go ahead and smash everything!

182
00:13:18,400 --> 00:13:19,400
Dan Hui.

183
00:13:20,800 --> 00:13:22,210
What are you doing here?

184
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,040
I'm so sorry.

185
00:13:26,340 --> 00:13:29,110
- Why?
- I should've checked in more often.

186
00:13:29,910 --> 00:13:31,350
I found out too late...

187
00:13:32,220 --> 00:13:34,120
that you were this sick
and all alone.

188
00:13:36,090 --> 00:13:38,560
I'm sorry, Dan Hui.

189
00:13:38,560 --> 00:13:40,490
No matter what it takes,

190
00:13:40,790 --> 00:13:41,890
I'll make you better.

191
00:13:42,730 --> 00:13:45,760
So you can't give up either. Okay?

192
00:13:46,700 --> 00:13:48,530
Promise me already.

193
00:13:49,900 --> 00:13:51,370
I'm scared that you'll leave me.

194
00:13:52,040 --> 00:13:55,570
I'm so scared
that you'll leave me all alone.

195
00:14:05,420 --> 00:14:06,450
Back then,

196
00:14:08,320 --> 00:14:09,590
the misery...

197
00:14:10,550 --> 00:14:12,320
should have ended with just me.

198
00:14:14,260 --> 00:14:15,760
My selfish desire to live...

199
00:14:16,460 --> 00:14:18,260
made you unhappy too.

200
00:14:21,030 --> 00:14:22,870
How can you say that?

201
00:14:24,440 --> 00:14:26,900
You can't even be fully happy
because of me.

202
00:14:28,170 --> 00:14:30,010
You found someone you love,

203
00:14:30,610 --> 00:14:32,540
and all you're worried about
is my surgery bills.

204
00:14:34,710 --> 00:14:37,510
I can't live like this anymore,
chipping away at your life.

205
00:14:37,580 --> 00:14:38,580
So...

206
00:14:40,220 --> 00:14:42,450
you want me
to just let you die like this?

207
00:14:45,390 --> 00:14:47,760
How can I live alone without you?

208
00:14:49,060 --> 00:14:52,100
- Alone...
- What's wrong with being alone?

209
00:14:52,330 --> 00:14:55,500
That's just how life is.
You're not 12 anymore.

210
00:14:56,530 --> 00:14:59,600
You can live perfectly fine
even if I die.

211
00:15:05,280 --> 00:15:06,540
It's best for everyone...

212
00:15:08,580 --> 00:15:10,080
if I stop here.

213
00:15:11,650 --> 00:15:12,950
Stopping?

214
00:15:13,450 --> 00:15:14,920
How is that the best option?

215
00:15:16,820 --> 00:15:19,590
The best thing to do
is try everything we can.

216
00:15:22,590 --> 00:15:23,690
I'm...

217
00:15:25,530 --> 00:15:27,560
still like a 12-year-old kid.

218
00:15:30,470 --> 00:15:33,470
Dan Hui, a world without you
is too scary for me.

219
00:15:38,280 --> 00:15:40,980
That's why I can't give up
and run away.

220
00:15:42,980 --> 00:15:45,480
I can't live if I don't do this.

221
00:15:46,220 --> 00:15:48,050
So I have no choice
but to see it through to the end.

222
00:15:52,290 --> 00:15:53,290
What about you?

223
00:15:55,030 --> 00:15:58,560
Are you okay
with stopping like this?

224
00:16:00,960 --> 00:16:02,200
Are you really?

225
00:16:08,740 --> 00:16:10,370
I'm begging you, Dan Hui.

226
00:16:11,140 --> 00:16:13,110
Please, live for me.

227
00:16:20,020 --> 00:16:21,520
If I lose you,

228
00:16:24,250 --> 00:16:26,860
I might want to give up
on everything.

229
00:16:30,460 --> 00:16:32,200
Saving you will give me strength,

230
00:16:33,700 --> 00:16:35,630
and I need that strength
to protect my child too.

231
00:16:36,270 --> 00:16:37,600
Help me do that, Dan Hui.

232
00:17:03,160 --> 00:17:05,460
All the test results are normal,

233
00:17:05,900 --> 00:17:07,830
and she's two months along.

234
00:17:08,730 --> 00:17:09,730
Right.

235
00:17:11,100 --> 00:17:12,370
What about the special favor
I asked?

236
00:17:13,600 --> 00:17:17,570
I spoke to the country house manager
where your wife was staying,

237
00:17:18,410 --> 00:17:20,740
and he said no outsiders
came or went.

238
00:17:23,410 --> 00:17:25,220
Okay, good work.

239
00:17:27,580 --> 00:17:30,650
I told you everything
after I came back from the checkup.

240
00:17:31,160 --> 00:17:33,920
Why would you doubt me
and call someone else to check?

241
00:17:34,790 --> 00:17:37,660
And what was that special favor
you asked for?

242
00:17:38,230 --> 00:17:39,330
You don't need to know.

243
00:17:39,930 --> 00:17:42,100
I have to go back to the office.

244
00:17:43,930 --> 00:17:45,040
You get some rest.

245
00:17:45,340 --> 00:17:46,600
On a day like today,

246
00:17:47,770 --> 00:17:49,010
do you really have to go?

247
00:17:50,170 --> 00:17:53,080
I'm busy with
the Wooju Department Store deal.

248
00:17:54,410 --> 00:17:57,510
Our Adele needs to establish itself
as a luxury jewelry brand...

249
00:17:57,710 --> 00:18:00,450
before we can expand to fashion,
cosmetics, food, and bio.

250
00:18:00,450 --> 00:18:03,120
That's how we can paint
the bigger picture.

251
00:18:03,620 --> 00:18:04,720
Adele's future...

252
00:18:05,020 --> 00:18:09,190
- depends on this contract.
- Then...

253
00:18:09,730 --> 00:18:12,700
At least feel the baby
before you go.

254
00:18:21,340 --> 00:18:22,610
It's a little late,

255
00:18:23,340 --> 00:18:25,210
but we officially have an heir.

256
00:18:26,810 --> 00:18:30,910
Having an official heir,
unlike your late father-in-law,

257
00:18:31,950 --> 00:18:34,890
means you've won. Doesn't it?

258
00:18:39,620 --> 00:18:41,190
(Last Will and Testament)

259
00:18:48,770 --> 00:18:50,670
How dare you?

260
00:18:50,670 --> 00:18:53,500
How dare you lay a hand on my will?

261
00:18:57,440 --> 00:19:01,010
I can't just sit back
and let Munhwadang be taken away.

262
00:19:01,010 --> 00:19:02,810
Munhwadang...

263
00:19:02,810 --> 00:19:05,980
Munhwadang is our family business!

264
00:19:06,920 --> 00:19:08,920
You aren't even family.

265
00:19:09,190 --> 00:19:13,390
I'd never, ever give it to you!
You little...

266
00:19:13,390 --> 00:19:14,420
Wrong!

267
00:19:16,090 --> 00:19:17,090
You're wrong.

268
00:19:17,760 --> 00:19:20,860
I'm the one who made Munhwadang
what it is today.

269
00:19:22,030 --> 00:19:25,970
It's a success I achieved
by enduring so much humiliation.

270
00:19:26,500 --> 00:19:30,210
Munhwadang will be my stepping stone
for a bigger,

271
00:19:30,740 --> 00:19:32,510
brighter success.

272
00:19:33,480 --> 00:19:35,610
I will build
the biggest corporation...

273
00:19:36,880 --> 00:19:38,750
in this country,

274
00:19:39,580 --> 00:19:40,780
spanning every sector.

275
00:19:41,250 --> 00:19:43,650
You snake!

276
00:19:46,720 --> 00:19:47,860
Foolish old man.

277
00:19:48,590 --> 00:19:50,930
Fine. Just you wait.

278
00:19:51,560 --> 00:19:53,730
Whatever you achieve,

279
00:19:54,670 --> 00:19:59,200
it will surely be stolen
by someone else.

280
00:19:59,600 --> 00:20:02,240
You, too, will suffer...

281
00:20:02,410 --> 00:20:04,640
the exact same fate.

282
00:20:05,140 --> 00:20:06,610
Mark my words!

283
00:20:08,310 --> 00:20:09,380
We'll see about that.

284
00:20:19,060 --> 00:20:22,130
Adele's heir is right here.

285
00:20:22,130 --> 00:20:25,200
I'll give you the son
your father-in-law never had.

286
00:20:26,030 --> 00:20:27,030
A son?

287
00:20:28,130 --> 00:20:30,730
We don't know
whether it's a boy or a girl yet.

288
00:20:33,100 --> 00:20:36,070
Of course it's going to be a son.

289
00:20:37,070 --> 00:20:39,340
Forget it. It doesn't matter.

290
00:20:40,210 --> 00:20:42,410
Because soon my son,

291
00:20:42,750 --> 00:20:46,120
the heir to Adele, will be born.

292
00:20:46,380 --> 00:20:47,420
What?

293
00:20:47,720 --> 00:20:50,450
Don't tell me you're going to
name that wretch's brat your heir.

294
00:20:50,450 --> 00:20:51,560
Watch your mouth!

295
00:20:52,820 --> 00:20:54,960
He's a precious son
I was finally blessed with.

296
00:20:57,630 --> 00:20:59,130
Just you try bringing him here.

297
00:20:59,130 --> 00:21:01,670
I'm your wife, the lady of Adele!

298
00:21:02,070 --> 00:21:04,500
My child is the true heir to Adele!

299
00:21:06,040 --> 00:21:07,040
Darn it.

300
00:21:09,810 --> 00:21:11,240
(Dongwoo University Hospital)

301
00:21:27,620 --> 00:21:28,630
Dan Hui.

302
00:21:31,330 --> 00:21:32,860
What are you doing here again?

303
00:21:33,560 --> 00:21:35,630
Myung Hui asked me to.

304
00:21:36,070 --> 00:21:38,040
You see her
as a big sister so naturally,

305
00:21:38,040 --> 00:21:39,270
even though you're the same age.

306
00:21:39,470 --> 00:21:41,470
We've been friends for ten years,
since middle school.

307
00:21:41,470 --> 00:21:44,780
So your big sister's my big sister,
and my little brother's yours.

308
00:21:44,780 --> 00:21:46,310
That's just how it is with us.

309
00:21:46,610 --> 00:21:49,010
I guess that's my famous loyalty.

310
00:21:49,580 --> 00:21:52,250
Without my loyalty,
I'm just skin and bones.

311
00:21:52,820 --> 00:21:54,120
That's how I can wear a size zero.

312
00:21:59,120 --> 00:22:02,160
You made the right choice.
Once you have the surgery in Seoul,

313
00:22:02,230 --> 00:22:03,460
I'm sure it'll go well.

314
00:22:03,460 --> 00:22:05,860
Myung Hui's devotion
didn't go unseen.

315
00:22:06,100 --> 00:22:07,700
It's about time
the universe noticed.

316
00:22:09,200 --> 00:22:10,270
Right.

317
00:22:15,810 --> 00:22:19,080
Wait here.
I'll go check if our cab is here.

318
00:22:33,660 --> 00:22:34,790
Up there in the sky,

319
00:22:35,790 --> 00:22:37,730
if someone really is listening,

320
00:22:41,130 --> 00:22:43,700
you must already know.

321
00:22:47,770 --> 00:22:50,670
I have never once been okay.

322
00:22:55,080 --> 00:22:56,550
I was always in pain,

323
00:22:58,420 --> 00:22:59,520
I was scared,

324
00:23:03,220 --> 00:23:04,860
and I wanted to live.

325
00:23:08,730 --> 00:23:10,190
Please, let me live.

326
00:23:13,060 --> 00:23:14,330
So I can stay by my sister's side.

327
00:23:15,570 --> 00:23:17,230
So I can protect her.

328
00:23:18,170 --> 00:23:19,270
Please help me.

329
00:23:30,250 --> 00:23:32,080
Well, Jung Ran...

330
00:23:36,290 --> 00:23:38,320
Why does this have to be
so darn delicious?

331
00:23:39,220 --> 00:23:41,390
They say these cravings mean a girl.

332
00:23:41,860 --> 00:23:44,060
What if I have a girl
when she's having a boy?

333
00:23:44,460 --> 00:23:47,100
You can forget about an heir.
He wouldn't even acknowledge her.

334
00:23:47,560 --> 00:23:48,800
There's no way.

335
00:23:50,470 --> 00:23:52,840
Thinking there's no way
is exactly how you get blindsided.

336
00:23:55,640 --> 00:23:58,680
I guess I have no choice
but to take care of it.

337
00:23:59,640 --> 00:24:00,640
Take care of it?

338
00:24:02,980 --> 00:24:06,580
You mean you'll leave Tae Ho
and be with me?

339
00:24:07,520 --> 00:24:09,390
My child will be Tae Ho's only child.

340
00:24:10,250 --> 00:24:11,250
What?

341
00:24:12,460 --> 00:24:13,590
Park Tae Ho's child?

342
00:24:16,630 --> 00:24:19,630
I'll take everything Park Tae Ho has
and hand it all to my child.

343
00:24:20,630 --> 00:24:22,530
It doesn't matter
if it's a son or a daughter,

344
00:24:23,330 --> 00:24:26,170
as long as they become
Adele's heir and owner.

345
00:24:26,870 --> 00:24:28,940
Adele's heir and owner?

346
00:24:33,240 --> 00:24:35,150
Rather than live
my whole life with regret,

347
00:24:35,780 --> 00:24:37,280
I'm going to do what I have to.

348
00:24:43,720 --> 00:24:46,020
Why are you giving me
that look again?

349
00:24:46,590 --> 00:24:48,590
What are you plotting now?

350
00:25:10,980 --> 00:25:12,380
Even if you don't have an appetite,

351
00:25:13,350 --> 00:25:14,950
you have to think of the baby.

352
00:25:15,650 --> 00:25:17,920
Here, have a bite.

353
00:25:20,720 --> 00:25:21,730
Right.

354
00:25:30,800 --> 00:25:33,200
I'm putting you out, aren't I?

355
00:25:34,070 --> 00:25:35,070
I'm sorry.

356
00:25:37,870 --> 00:25:39,540
I know I'm being a burden,

357
00:25:41,280 --> 00:25:43,450
but I just can't find the courage
to go back to that house.

358
00:25:44,110 --> 00:25:45,950
Tell me about it.

359
00:25:47,650 --> 00:25:50,220
If I were you, I couldn't set foot
in that house either.

360
00:25:51,620 --> 00:25:54,460
Just hearing about it
makes my blood boil.

361
00:25:55,190 --> 00:25:57,260
I can't imagine how you must feel.

362
00:25:58,660 --> 00:26:02,330
You can stay here for the rest
of your life if you want,

363
00:26:03,270 --> 00:26:04,270
so just make yourself at home.

364
00:26:10,810 --> 00:26:12,140
Thank you, ma'am.

365
00:26:22,050 --> 00:26:23,250
Nurse Myung Hui.

366
00:26:24,020 --> 00:26:27,220
Are you crying
because the baby's clothes got ruined?

367
00:26:28,490 --> 00:26:31,530
I made it pretty for you,

368
00:26:32,360 --> 00:26:33,860
so don't cry.

369
00:26:47,910 --> 00:26:48,950
It's beautiful.

370
00:26:49,710 --> 00:26:52,780
Really?
So you won't cry anymore, right?

371
00:26:54,550 --> 00:26:55,550
I won't.

372
00:26:57,850 --> 00:27:01,660
The stains on my heart...

373
00:27:02,530 --> 00:27:04,590
have turned
into something beautiful,

374
00:27:06,600 --> 00:27:09,170
so I won't cry anymore.

375
00:27:10,100 --> 00:27:11,570
I think I can be brave now.

376
00:27:15,170 --> 00:27:17,240
- Thank you.
- Sure.

377
00:28:02,920 --> 00:28:06,090
I think that's the house over there.

378
00:28:09,160 --> 00:28:11,660
I know you wanted to come as soon
as you got out of the hospital,

379
00:28:12,230 --> 00:28:14,160
but we should've called first.

380
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:16,800
Showing up like this
might startle Myung Hui.

381
00:28:17,670 --> 00:28:20,170
I wanted to see
what her life was really like.

382
00:28:20,600 --> 00:28:23,770
How she's living,
and what the man she loves is like.

383
00:28:24,210 --> 00:28:27,640
- I had to see it with my own eyes.
- I get it.

384
00:28:27,710 --> 00:28:29,180
- Let's go.
- Okay.

385
00:29:05,220 --> 00:29:06,820
Do they live here too?

386
00:29:10,520 --> 00:29:11,520
Where are you going?

387
00:29:14,220 --> 00:29:15,230
Myung Hui.

388
00:29:18,660 --> 00:29:19,660
Myung Hui?

389
00:29:22,200 --> 00:29:23,200
Myung Hui.

390
00:29:28,300 --> 00:29:29,310
Myung Hui!

391
00:29:30,140 --> 00:29:31,140
Dan Hui.

392
00:29:36,750 --> 00:29:37,950
- Myung Hui!
- What?

393
00:29:38,980 --> 00:29:41,350
Myung Hui, come on. Wake up!

394
00:29:41,620 --> 00:29:44,920
Myung Hui, what's wrong? Myung Hui!

395
00:29:45,020 --> 00:29:46,720
Myung Hui, open your eyes!

396
00:29:47,560 --> 00:29:48,560
Myung Hui!

397
00:29:48,930 --> 00:29:50,460
- Myung Hui!
- Oh no, what do we do?

398
00:29:51,830 --> 00:29:52,830
Myung Hui, what's wrong?

399
00:29:55,900 --> 00:29:56,900
(Emergency Medical Center)

400
00:29:58,070 --> 00:30:00,100
Help! Somebody, please!

401
00:30:02,770 --> 00:30:04,040
(Emergency Medical Center)

402
00:30:09,980 --> 00:30:11,310
She's a pregnant patient in her 20s.

403
00:30:11,950 --> 00:30:14,480
There's no visible trauma,
but she's pulseless, not breathing.

404
00:30:14,950 --> 00:30:16,090
Please save her, Doctor.

405
00:30:29,470 --> 00:30:30,470
Please.

406
00:30:39,540 --> 00:30:42,750
I'm sorry.
The patient has passed away.

407
00:30:44,280 --> 00:30:46,550
No. You can still save her.

408
00:30:47,780 --> 00:30:49,750
My sister isn't one
to give up so easily.

409
00:30:50,150 --> 00:30:51,150
Myung Hui.

410
00:30:52,160 --> 00:30:54,520
Myung Hui, you told me.

411
00:30:55,930 --> 00:30:58,630
You said you'd do what it takes
to live, until the very end.

412
00:30:58,830 --> 00:31:02,000
Myung Hui!

413
00:31:02,530 --> 00:31:05,200
Myung Hui, come on. Breathe.

414
00:31:05,770 --> 00:31:07,740
Myung Hui, please.

415
00:31:15,180 --> 00:31:16,180
The baby's alive.

416
00:31:21,350 --> 00:31:22,590
The baby's alive!

417
00:31:54,820 --> 00:31:57,820
(Pearl in Red)

418
00:31:57,950 --> 00:32:00,990
Both babies were born the same day,
at the exact same time.

419
00:32:01,260 --> 00:32:04,360
- The baby's alive.
- Take the baby away right now.

420
00:32:04,890 --> 00:32:06,730
Hurry, before Park Tae Ho
gets to him first!

421
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,500
What if we get caught?

422
00:32:08,500 --> 00:32:10,400
He just lost the son
he'd been waiting for.

423
00:32:10,470 --> 00:32:12,000
Do you think Tae Ho
will just let it go?

424
00:32:12,070 --> 00:32:15,910
Don't worry. I know someone
who can handle this without a trace.

425
00:32:16,340 --> 00:32:19,510
I can't lose the baby
my sister died to protect.

426
00:32:19,580 --> 00:32:21,440
That's right! I killed her.

427
00:32:21,710 --> 00:32:22,710
Dan Hui!

428
00:32:22,780 --> 00:32:24,550
I'm done begging for your love.

429
00:32:24,550 --> 00:32:27,520
My child will be Adele's heir
and take over.

430
00:32:28,120 --> 00:32:29,520
That's all I'm living for now.

431
00:32:29,820 --> 00:32:31,820
(Subtitles are provided by KOCOWA.)
